\paragraph{Negation}
We define |rnot R = R => bot|, leading to the pointwise meaning |b((rnot R))a <=> not(b R a)|.
From the Galois connection of |R=>S| one immediately derives that of negation,
\begin{eqnarray}
	|X atmost (rnot R)| & |<=>| & |rnot X atleast R|
	\label{eq:210110b}
\end{eqnarray}
cf.
\begin{eqnarray*}
\start
