\end{eqnarray*}
where $\larrow A f A$ for some $A$,
we will say that any \textbf{solution} to this equation ---
that is, any $a_0 \in A$ such that
\begin{eqnarray*}
a_0 &=& f\ a_0
\end{eqnarray*}
is a \textbf{fixpoint} of $f$.
\end{Slide}

\section{Equations versus recursion}
Equation
\(
\red
x = \ap f x
